text: Anna Grudko (; born 9 February 1990) is a retired Russian artistic gymnast. She is the 2006 European champion on vault, and a member of the Russian team at the 2006 World Championships that won the bronze medal. Additionally, she won bronze at the 2006 European Championships with the Russian team and at the 2007 European Championships on vault. == References == Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Russian female artistic gymnasts Category:Medalists at the World Artistic Gymnastics Championships Category:People from Severodvinsk
